# Implementation Plan - Mobile-first Polished Mood Dashboard (Issue 06)

Implement a high-fidelity, mobile-first design matching the visual language of [image.png](file:///c:/Users/Surya/Documents/mental-wellness-tracker/image.png). We will reorganize the React frontend into a premium single-page application with a tab-based view controller, matching the three mockup screens: Landing Screen, Home Dashboard, and Mood Calendar.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **View Controllers**:
> We will introduce a view controller state `activeTab` with the following screens:
> 1. **`landing` (Landing Screen)**: Playful colored shapes with cartoon expressions, large bold header, and a pill button CTA: *"Not Sure About Your Mood? Let Us Help! →"*.
> 2. **`home` (Home Dashboard)**: Date header, student greeting, quick-mood selection buttons, metrics grid (Sleep Duration bar graphs, Stress Indicator sparklines, interactive Yes/No Quiz), and the Journal entry form.
> 3. **`calendar` (Mood Calendar)**: Month day grid (days with entries show the color-coded emoji), dominant Monthly Mood Summary card, and supplementary metrics (Activity steps, Therapy sessions, Focus score).
> 4. **`trends` (Insights & Coping)**: Preserves the detailed Weekly Mood Pulse SVG chart, Stress Trigger modal triggers, and the daily Coping Companion guide.
>
> **Interactive Quiz**:
> We will implement a mock interactive quiz card that allows the student to answer Yes/No questions (e.g., *"Have you been sleeping well recently?"*, *"Are you studying more than 8 hours daily?"*) and provides summary guidance at the end.
>
> **Interactive Metrics**:
> The Sleep Duration and Stress Indicator widgets will dynamically render mini-bar-graphs or sparklines using the actual database entries loaded from the backend!

